1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,891
Think about the grape example the next time you're selling yourself.

2
00:00:04,161 --> 00:00:10,130
Properly packaged, you have a better chance to make the sale, and at a higher price.

3
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:16,450
The point is, the better you are packaged, the more public acceptance you will receive.

4
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:23,250
Tomorrow, watch who is shown the most respect and courtesy in restaurants, on buses,

5
00:00:23,281 --> 00:00:26,611
in crowded lobbies, in stores, and at work.

6
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:33,810
People look at another person, make a quick and often subconscious appraisal, and then treat them accordingly.

7
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:38,931
We look at some people and respond with the, hey, Mac, attitude.

8
00:00:39,121 --> 00:00:43,011
We look at others and respond with the, yes, sir, feeling.

9
00:00:43,521 --> 00:00:46,850
Yes, a person's appearance definitely talks.

10
00:00:47,041 --> 00:00:50,611
The well-dressed person's appearance says positive things.

11
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:56,850
It tells people, here is an important person, intelligent, prosperous, and dependable.

12
00:00:57,041 --> 00:01:00,531
This man can be looked up to, admired, trusted.

13
00:01:00,721 --> 00:01:03,730
He respects himself, and I respect him.

14
00:01:04,401 --> 00:01:08,131
The shabby-looking fellow's appearance says negative things.

15
00:01:08,161 --> 00:01:11,570
It says, here is a person who isn't doing well.

16
00:01:11,681 --> 00:01:14,531
He's careless, inefficient, unimportant.

17
00:01:14,721 --> 00:01:16,611
He's just an average person.

18
00:01:16,721 --> 00:01:19,330
He deserves no special consideration.

19
00:01:19,521 --> 00:01:21,731
He's used to being pushed around.

20
00:01:22,241 --> 00:01:28,771
When I stress respect your appearance in training programs, almost always I am asked the question,

21
00:01:29,121 --> 00:01:39,251
I'm sold, appearance is important, but how do you expect me to afford the kind of clothing that really makes me feel right and that causes others to look up to me?

22
00:01:40,241 --> 00:01:42,531
That question puzzles many people.

23
00:01:42,641 --> 00:01:44,771
It plagued me for a long time.

24
00:01:44,961 --> 00:01:47,330
But the answer is really a simple one.

25
00:01:47,521 --> 00:01:50,690
Pay twice as much and buy half as many.

26
00:01:50,881 --> 00:01:54,371
Commit this answer to memory, then practice it.

27
00:01:54,561 --> 00:02:00,371
Apply it to hats, suits, shoes, socks, coats, everything you wear.

28
00:02:00,961 --> 00:02:06,450
Insofar as appearance is concerned, quality is far more important than quantity.

29
00:02:06,561 --> 00:02:14,371
When you practice this principle, you'll find that both your respect for yourself and the respect of others for you will zoom upward,

30
00:02:14,561 --> 00:02:20,850
and you'll find you're actually ahead money-wise when you pay twice as much and buy half as many,

31
00:02:20,961 --> 00:02:22,611
because 1.

32
00:02:22,801 --> 00:02:28,210
Your garments will last more than twice as long because they are more than twice as good,

33
00:02:28,241 --> 00:02:32,051
and as a rule they will show quality as long as they last.

34
00:02:32,051 --> 00:02:33,251
2.

35
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:36,131
What you buy will stay in style longer.

36
00:02:36,321 --> 00:02:38,210
Better clothing always does.

37
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:39,570
3.

38
00:02:39,681 --> 00:02:41,491
You'll get better advice.

39
00:02:41,681 --> 00:02:52,771
Merchants selling $200 suits are usually much more interested in helping you find the garment that is just right for you than are merchants selling $100 suits.

40
00:02:53,361 --> 00:02:57,810
Remember, your appearance talks to you and it talks to others.

41
00:02:58,001 --> 00:03:02,131
Make certain it says, here is a person who has self-respect.

42
00:03:02,241 --> 00:03:03,411
He's important.

43
00:03:03,521 --> 00:03:04,771
Treat him that way.

44
00:03:05,281 --> 00:03:11,330
You owe it to others, but more important, you owe it to yourself to look your best.

45
00:03:11,761 --> 00:03:13,731
You are what you think you are.

46
00:03:13,921 --> 00:03:18,210
If your appearance makes you think you're inferior, you are inferior.

47
00:03:18,321 --> 00:03:21,411
If it makes you think small, you are small.

48
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:25,090
Look your best and you will think and act your best.

49
00:03:27,921 --> 00:03:30,210
Think your work is important.
